<br>
In terms of the quests to get into HOH, COD etc.  These quests are long and intricate.  They require multiple rare spawns, and if you work hard at it, you can probably finish the quests in a few days if lucky.  The reward for finishing the quest, access to a zone with no group.  Most times those Ubah guilds group together, so you will spend hours LFG in HOH.  Unless you are Ubah or have Ubah friends there is no current reason to do the quest, until HOH/COD become pickup or common zones.<br>
<br>
As far as wheter its easier to kill the dragon or do the quest.  Question, what was easier killing Arch Lych or Luclin Shard camping.  Answer killing Arch Lych.  Any bet more people get into HOH on open raids killing dragons than by doing that quest.  1 night and you and all your friends get flagged, versus weeks of camping for you and all your friends.<br>
<br>
Having spectral drop in Tier 1, might be silly when most of the players who need those spells have access to Tier 2 zones.  However, having spectral only drop in Tier 3 zones when most do not have access is even worse.  Verant please fix, allow spectral to drop in Storm/Valor at a reasonable rate.  Give casters a reason to level.<br>
<br>
